Anonymous Thu 18 Jul 2024 21:52:24 No.67505328 Report

>>67505144
quick tip, anon, if you're going to greentext in first person avoid using the word "I", and at the very beginning state whose perspective it is. the word 'me' is still acceptable
>be me
>working in department store for about a year now
>get a new hire, an anthro girl
>blahblah
>try to make nice with her, but she just blah blah
>initially take it as awkwardness, despite that she really likes to be near me
and so on so forth. in my experience most anons like to self-insert, which makes reading first person and not being able to do so an unpleasant task. using the word "I" turns it from a story they can imagine themselves in into a story you're telling me about you which is less interesting
